						               													<description>Longhorns graze on the meadows, but if a settlement is built, they must move to somewhere else. Sometimes that goes without any problems, but if you push too hard it can cause problems for everyone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fortunately caravans visits the settlements with new supplies. Trade with them, so you can easily get other goods. Finally ranches are built in the settlements. To build a ranch is a great investment, but it unlocks a permanent special ability. Ranches also provide considerable prestige and that is needed to win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The expansion consists of three module which can be combined with the base game and any other expansion.&amp;#10;Module 1: Ranches&amp;#10;Players need to build 3 ranches and 12 settlement to win the game.&amp;#10;Rances cost a lot of resources but give player special abilities during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Module 2: New supplies&amp;#10;During the build action players can trade resources for other resources.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Module 3: Longhorn&amp;#10;Longhorn meeples are placed on the board during the setup.&amp;#10;When building a settlement on a longhorn space, the longhorn needs to move.&amp;#10;Each turn a longhorn is move a rule is changed in the game (sometimes good, sometimes bad)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
